  "title": "An Assassin Foretold at Bodkins Antiquities",
  "summary": "In the lobby of Bodkins Antiquities, the brooding CSA board member Geophreigh Smitherbodkins contemplates a prized sabacc deck when the executive Miranda Jabs arrives to persuade him to drop his Direx vote, a request he refuses on principle. Their veiled conversation is interrupted by Lanze, an armored Mandalorian of clan Beviin, who buys children's picture books and probes Smitherbodkins about the new Prex and his standing in the Corporate Sector before leaving with only a business card. Meanwhile Jabs, feigning interest in an exorbitant Huttese king's pen, discovers to her disgust that it writes in a foul-smelling ink. Once Lanze departs and Smitherbodkins raises a privacy field, Jabs reveals the true purpose of her visit: the deranged Toydarian Qwynt, upset over the emergency Direx meeting, may be plotting to kill Smitherbodkins before he can be voted out. Smitherbodkins, weary of the bungled attempts on his life, takes the warning in stride, and the two conclude their business with Jabs purchasing the offensive pen and desk as a 'gift' to pass along to an unfortunate recipient, sealing their quiet conspiratorial understanding.",
